Common.Strapline.Common.Text: THE NEW HEART OF RUNDLE MALL

Common.LongDescription.Common.Text:
The striking redevelopment of the ground floor at 11 Waymouth Street is now complete. The exciting transformation allows passage through the building along the new laneway which runs into the landscaped plaza.

Tenancy 1, which has been leased on local coffee specialist My Kingdom For A Horse, has both foyer and Waymouth Street access and will be serving from their uniquely designed kiosk.

Located on the corner of the new laneway Hello Sarnie are now open and trading. Adding to the mix will be Sit Lo and Sushi Sushi later in the year. 

Two opportunities remain. Our bespoke fully fitted caravan is available, just 12 sqm the tenancy is fully equipped for a F&B use. Secondly, Stylecraft will be relocating to the mezzanine floor of the development so their current space of 232 sqm will be available from January 2021. The tenancy has substantial Waymouth Street frontage and benefits from stunning double height façade and ceilings through. We are seeking retail or service providers for this space.
